37// Script describes a script which has been added to the VM.
38class Script : public TorqueGeneratedScript<Script, Struct> {
39 public:
40 // Script ID used for temporary scripts, which shouldn't be added to the
41 // script list.
42 static constexpr int kTemporaryScriptId = -2;
43
44 NEVER_READ_ONLY_SPACE
45 // Script types.
46 enum class Type {
47 kNative = 0,
48 kExtension = 1,
49 kNormal = 2,
50#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
51 kWasm = 3,
52#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
53 kInspector = 4
54 };
55
56 // Script compilation types.
57 enum class CompilationType { kHost = 0, kEval = 1 };
58
59 // Script compilation state.
60 enum class CompilationState { kInitial = 0, kCompiled = 1 };
61
62 // [type]: the script type.
63 DECL_PRIMITIVE_ACCESSORS(type, Type)
64
65 DECL_ACCESSORS(eval_from_shared_or_wrapped_arguments, Tagged<Object>)
66
67 // [eval_from_shared]: for eval scripts the shared function info for the
68 // function from which eval was called.
69 DECL_ACCESSORS(eval_from_shared, Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo>)
70
71 // [wrapped_arguments]: for the list of arguments in a wrapped script.
72 DECL_ACCESSORS(wrapped_arguments, Tagged<FixedArray>)
73
74 // Whether the script is implicitly wrapped in a function.
75 inline bool is_wrapped() const;
76
77 // Whether the eval_from_shared field is set with a shared function info
78 // for the eval site.
79 inline bool has_eval_from_shared() const;
80
81 // [eval_from_position]: the source position in the code for the function
82 // from which eval was called, as positive integer. Or the code offset in the
83 // code from which eval was called, as negative integer.
84 DECL_INT_ACCESSORS(eval_from_position)
85
86 // [shared_function_infos]: weak fixed array containing all shared
87 // function infos created from this script.
88 DECL_ACCESSORS(shared_function_infos, Tagged<WeakFixedArray>)
89
90 inline int shared_function_info_count() const;
91
92#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
93 // [wasm_breakpoint_infos]: the list of {BreakPointInfo} objects describing
94 // all WebAssembly breakpoints for modules/instances managed via this script.
95 // This must only be called if the type of this script is TYPE_WASM.
96 DECL_ACCESSORS(wasm_breakpoint_infos, Tagged<FixedArray>)
97 inline bool has_wasm_breakpoint_infos() const;
98
99 // [wasm_native_module]: the wasm {NativeModule} this script belongs to.
100 // This must only be called if the type of this script is TYPE_WASM.
101 DECL_ACCESSORS(wasm_managed_native_module, Tagged<Object>)
102 inline wasm::NativeModule* wasm_native_module() const;
103
104 // [wasm_weak_instance_list]: the list of all {WasmInstanceObject} being
105 // affected by breakpoints that are managed via this script.
106 // This must only be called if the type of this script is TYPE_WASM.
107 DECL_ACCESSORS(wasm_weak_instance_list, Tagged<WeakArrayList>)
108
109 // [break_on_entry] (wasm only): whether an instrumentation breakpoint is set
110 // for this script; this information will be transferred to existing and
111 // future instances to make sure that we stop before executing any code in
112 // this wasm module.
113 inline bool break_on_entry() const;
114 inline void set_break_on_entry(bool value);
115
116 // Check if the script contains any Asm modules.
117 bool ContainsAsmModule();
118#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
119
120 // [compilation_type]: how the the script was compiled. Encoded in the
121 // 'flags' field.
122 inline CompilationType compilation_type();
123 inline void set_compilation_type(CompilationType type);
124
125 inline bool produce_compile_hints() const;
126 inline void set_produce_compile_hints(bool produce_compile_hints);
127
128 inline bool deserialized() const;
129 inline void set_deserialized(bool value);
130
131 // [compilation_state]: determines whether the script has already been
132 // compiled. Encoded in the 'flags' field.
133 inline CompilationState compilation_state();
134 inline void set_compilation_state(CompilationState state);
135
136 // [is_repl_mode]: whether this script originated from a REPL via debug
137 // evaluate and therefore has different semantics, e.g. re-declaring let.
138 inline bool is_repl_mode() const;
139 inline void set_is_repl_mode(bool value);
140
141 // [origin_options]: optional attributes set by the embedder via ScriptOrigin,
142 // and used by the embedder to make decisions about the script. V8 just passes
143 // this through. Encoded in the 'flags' field.
144 inline v8::ScriptOriginOptions origin_options();
145 inline void set_origin_options(ScriptOriginOptions origin_options);
146
147 DECL_ACCESSORS(compiled_lazy_function_positions, Tagged<Object>)
148
149 // If script source is an external string, check that the underlying
150 // resource is accessible. Otherwise, always return true.
151 inline bool HasValidSource();
152
153 // If the script has a non-empty sourceURL comment.
154 inline bool HasSourceURLComment() const;
155
156 // Streaming compilation only attaches the source to the Script upon
157 // finalization. This predicate returns true, if this script may still be
158 // unfinalized.
159 inline bool IsMaybeUnfinalized(Isolate* isolate) const;
160
161 Tagged<Object> GetNameOrSourceURL();
162 static Handle<String> GetScriptHash(Isolate* isolate, Handle<Script> script,
163 bool forceForInspector);
164
165 // Retrieve source position from where eval was called.
166 static int GetEvalPosition(Isolate* isolate, Handle<Script> script);
167
168 // Initialize line_ends array with source code positions of line ends if
169 // it doesn't exist yet.
170 static inline void InitLineEnds(Isolate* isolate, Handle<Script> script);
171 static inline void InitLineEnds(LocalIsolate* isolate, Handle<Script> script);
172
173 // Obtain line ends as a vector, without modifying the script object
174 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE static String::LineEndsVector GetLineEnds(
175 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Script> script);
176
177 inline bool has_line_ends() const;
178
179 // Will initialize the line ends if required.
180 static void SetSource(Isolate* isolate, Handle<Script> script,
181 Handle<String> source);
182
183 bool inline CanHaveLineEnds() const;
184
185 // Carries information about a source position.
186 struct PositionInfo {
187 PositionInfo() : line(-1), column(-1), line_start(-1), line_end(-1) {}
188
189 int line; // Zero-based line number.
190 int column; // Zero-based column number.
191 int line_start; // Position of first character in line.
192 int line_end; // Position of final linebreak character in line.
193 };
194
195 // Specifies whether to add offsets to position infos.
196 enum class OffsetFlag { kNoOffset, kWithOffset };
197
198 // Retrieves information about the given position, optionally with an offset.
199 // Returns false on failure, and otherwise writes into the given info object
200 // on success.
201 // The static method should is preferable for handlified callsites because it
202 // initializes the line ends array, avoiding expensive recomputations.
203 // The non-static version is not allocating and safe for unhandlified
204 // callsites.
205 static bool GetPositionInfo(Handle<Script> script, int position,
206 PositionInfo* info,
207 OffsetFlag offset_flag = OffsetFlag::kWithOffset);
208 static bool GetLineColumnWithLineEnds(
209 int position, int& line, int& column,
210 const String::LineEndsVector& line_ends);
211 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE bool GetPositionInfo(
212 int position, PositionInfo* info,
213 OffsetFlag offset_flag = OffsetFlag::kWithOffset) const;
214 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE bool GetPositionInfoWithLineEnds(
215 int position, PositionInfo* info, const String::LineEndsVector& line_ends,
216 OffsetFlag offset_flag = OffsetFlag::kWithOffset) const;
217 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE void AddPositionInfoOffset(
218 PositionInfo* info,
219 OffsetFlag offset_flag = OffsetFlag::kWithOffset) const;
220
221 // Tells whether this script should be subject to debugging, e.g. for
222 // - scope inspection
223 // - internal break points
224 // - coverage and type profile
225 // - error stack trace
226 bool IsSubjectToDebugging() const;
227
228 bool IsUserJavaScript() const;
229
230 // Wrappers for GetPositionInfo
231 static int GetColumnNumber(Handle<Script> script, int code_offset);
232 int GetColumnNumber(int code_pos) const;
233 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE static int GetLineNumber(Handle<Script> script,
234 int code_offset);
235 int GetLineNumber(int code_pos) const;
236
237 // Look through the list of existing shared function infos to find one
238 // that matches the function literal. Return empty handle if not found.
239 template <typename IsolateT>
240 static MaybeHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> FindSharedFunctionInfo(
241 Handle<Script> script, IsolateT* isolate,
242 FunctionLiteral* function_literal);
243
244 // Iterate over all script objects on the heap.
245 class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE Iterator {
246 public:
247 explicit Iterator(Isolate* isolate);
248 Iterator(const Iterator&) = delete;
249 Iterator& operator=(const Iterator&) = delete;
250 Tagged<Script> Next();
251
252 private:
253 WeakArrayList::Iterator iterator_;
254 };
255
256 // Dispatched behavior.
257 DECL_PRINTER(Script)
258 DECL_VERIFIER(Script)
259
260 using BodyDescriptor = StructBodyDescriptor;
261
262 private:
263 template <typename LineEndsContainer>
264 bool GetPositionInfoInternal(const LineEndsContainer& ends, int position,
265 Script::PositionInfo* info,
266 const DisallowGarbageCollection& no_gc) const;
267
268 friend Factory;
269 friend FactoryBase<Factory>;
270 friend FactoryBase<LocalFactory>;
271
272 // Hide torque-generated accessor, use Script::SetSource instead.
273 using TorqueGeneratedScript::set_source;
274
275 // Bit positions in the flags field.
276 DEFINE_TORQUE_GENERATED_SCRIPT_FLAGS()

281 EXPORT_TEMPLATE_DECLARE(V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE)
282 static void V8_PRESERVE_MOST
283 InitLineEndsInternal(IsolateT* isolate, Handle<Script> script);
284};
